VALUES ('64fd5948-ca5d-4acb-8b7f-bf89f4d5f7e7', 'Which choice most logically completes the text?', 'An archaeologist excavating a buried settlement reported that pottery decorated with a particular spiral motif appears only in layers deposited after the construction of the settlement''s large central well, never in layers below it. She also established that the layers of the site were deposited in strict chronological order, with deeper layers always older than those above them, and that the spiral motif was never used anywhere in the region before this settlement existed. A fragment bearing the spiral motif was then found at a second, undated site nearby. From the archaeologist''s findings, it follows that this fragment ______', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"was produced no earlier than the construction of the settlement''s central well.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"The motif exists only after the well''s construction, so any motif-bearing fragment postdates it."},{"id":"B","text":"was carried to the second site by traders from the first settlement.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Trade routes and transport are not established by the findings."},{"id":"C","text":"is older than the deepest layers of the first settlement.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"This contradicts that the motif never appears below the well''s layer."},{"id":"D","text":"proves the second site was inhabited longer than the first.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Relative occupation lengths cannot be inferred from one fragment."}]'::jsonb, 'A', 'Step 1 — Date the motif''s origin
The spiral motif appears {{yellow:only in layers deposited after the construction of the settlement''s large central well}} and was {{yellow:never used anywhere in the region before this settlement existed}}.
Step 2 — Apply to the new fragment
Because the motif came into existence only after the well was built, any fragment bearing it—wherever found—must postdate the well''s construction.
Distractor analysis:
- B: The findings say nothing about traders or how the fragment traveled to the second site.
- C: The motif never appears below the well''s layer, so a motif fragment cannot predate the deepest layers.
- D: A single fragment gives no information about how long either site was occupied.', 'When did this motif first come into existence, and can any object bearing it be older than that?', 'Information and Ideas', 'Inferences', 'reading_writing', 'information', 'INF', NULL, 'hard', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"generator":"scholaris_ai_v1","model":"gemma-4-26b-a4b-it","original":true,"explanation_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now())
